## Appendix E Asymptotic equivalents: background and known results

Preliminary background.In several proofs, we employ the concept of asymptotic equivalence of sequences of random matrices; see [12, 44, 49, 51]. This section provides a brief overview of the associated terminology and calculus principles.

**Definition E.1** (Asymptotic equivalence).: _Consider sequences \(\{\bm{A}_{p}\}_{p\geq 1}\) and \(\{\bm{B}_{p}\}_{p\geq 1}\) of (random or deterministic) matrices of growing dimensions. We say that \(\bm{A}_{p}\) and \(\bm{B}_{p}\) are equivalent and write \(\bm{A}_{p}\simeq\bm{B}_{p}\) if \(\lim_{p\to\infty}|\operatorname{tr}[\bm{C}_{p}(\bm{A}_{p}-\bm{B}_{p})]|=0\) almost surely for every sequence of random matrices \(\bm{C}_{p}\) independent to \(\bm{A}_{p}\) and \(\bm{B}_{p}\), with bounded trace norm such that \(\limsup_{p\to\infty}\|\bm{C}_{p}\|_{\operatorname{tr}}<\infty\) almost surely._

The notion of asymptotic equivalence of two sequences of random matrices above can be further extended to incorporate conditioning on another sequence of random matrices; see [12] for more details.

**Definition E.2** (Conditional asymptotic equivalence).: _Consider sequences \(\{\bm{A}_{p}\}_{p\geq 1}\), \(\{\bm{B}_{p}\}_{p\geq 1}\) and \(\{\bm{D}_{p}\}_{p\geq 1}\) of (random or deterministic) matrices of growing dimensions. We say that \(\bm{A}_{p}\) and \(\bm{B}_{p}\) are equivalent given \(\bm{D}_{p}\) and write \(\bm{A}_{p}\simeq\bm{B}_{p}\mid\bm{D}_{p}\) if \(\lim_{p\to\infty}|\operatorname{tr}[\bm{C}_{p}(\bm{A}_{p}-\bm{B}_{p})]|=0\) almost surely conditional on \(\{\bm{D}_{p}\}_{p\geq 1}\), i.e.,_

\[\mathbb{P}\left(\lim_{p\to\infty}|\operatorname{tr}[\bm{C}_{p}(\bm{A}_{p}-\bm{B} _{p})]|=0\,\bigg{|}\,\{\bm{D}_{p}\}_{p\geq 1}\right)=1,\]

_for any sequence of random matrices \(\bm{C}_{p}\) independent to \(\bm{A}_{p}\) and \(\bm{B}_{p}\) conditional on \(\bm{D}_{p}\), with bounded trace norm such that \(\limsup\|\bm{C}_{p}\|_{\operatorname{tr}}<\infty\) as \(p\to\infty\)._

Below we summarize the calculus rules for conditional asymptotic equivalence in Definition E.2. These are adapted from Lemma S.7.4 and S.7.6 of [12].

**Lemma E.3** (Calculus of asymptotic equivalents).: _Let \(\bm{A}_{p}\), \(\bm{B}_{p}\), \(\bm{C}_{p}\) and \(\bm{D}_{p}\) be sequences of random matrices. The calculus of asymptotic equivalents satisfies the following properties:_

1. _Equivalence: The relation_ \(\simeq\) _is an equivalence relation._
2. _Sum: If_ \(\bm{A}_{p}\simeq\bm{B}_{p}\mid\bm{E}_{p}\) _and_ \(\bm{C}_{p}\simeq\bm{D}_{p}\mid\bm{E}_{p}\)_, then_ \(\bm{A}_{p}+\bm{C}_{p}\simeq\bm{B}_{p}+\bm{D}_{p}\mid\bm{E}_{p}\)_._
3. _Product: If_ \(\bm{A}_{p}\) _has bounded operator norms such that_ \(\limsup_{p\to\infty}\|\bm{A}_{p}\|_{\mathrm{op}}<\infty\)_,_ \(\bm{A}_{p}\) _is conditional independent to_ \(\bm{B}_{p}\) _and_ \(\bm{C}_{p}\) _given_ \(\bm{E}_{p}\) _for_ \(p\geq 1\)_, and_ \(\bm{B}_{p}\simeq\bm{C}_{p}\mid\bm{E}_{p}\)_, then_ \(\bm{A}_{p}\bm{B}_{p}\simeq\bm{A}_{p}\bm{C}_{p}\mid\bm{E}_{p}\)_._
4. _Trace: If_ \(\bm{A}_{p}\simeq\bm{B}_{p}\mid\bm{E}_{p}\)_, then_ \(\mathrm{tr}[\bm{A}_{p}]/p-\mathrm{tr}[\bm{B}_{p}]/p\to 0\) _almost surely when conditioning on_ \(\bm{E}_{p}\)_._
